# Walmart Statistical Analysis

## Project Overview

This project analyzes Walmart Black Friday customer purchase behavior using statistical analysis, exploratory data analysis (EDA), and confidence interval estimation techniques.

The objective is to understand customer spending behavior across gender, marital status, and age groups using statistical inference and the Central Limit Theorem (CLT).

---

# Business Problem

Walmart wants to analyze customer purchase behavior during Black Friday sales to determine:

- Whether male and female customers spend differently
- Spending variations across marital status
- Spending behavior across age groups
- Population spending estimates using confidence intervals

The insights can help Walmart optimize promotions, customer targeting, and marketing strategies.

---

# Analysis Performed

- Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
- Missing Value Detection
- Outlier Analysis
- Gender-wise Purchase Analysis
- Confidence Interval Estimation
- Central Limit Theorem (CLT)
- Marital Status Analysis
- Age Group Analysis
- Statistical Inference

